column5: Well its almost that time, bow season opens at the end of the month.  How are people preparing, cleared shooting lanes on Saturday and spent sunday in bed paying for it.    I am on a great farm with deer from yearlings to a deer I  saw just south of the property that was about 210 non typical.   This is the best one I have seen there, hope he made it to this year cuz he is going to be an awesome 5 year old

Darren stop it,just stop it.The buck that is. Wish you luck my friend. Thats a real nice buck.  I havent been out,but the corn is planted on the northend this year and beans are all around the rest.I got feed for them.

The non typical i almost ran over a couple miles to te south of my stand is truly a record book animal. 10 inch drop ttine on te left side, 10 point with mass, and and an outside spread OFC 36 inches. Sat in front f my truck 5 feet away for 20 seconds staring at me.   never seen anything like it. Not even muley huinting, which he looked like

My hunting partner and I both made a pact to hunt more waterfowl at the start of the season, and hold off until late October, maybe November before we start beating the bush.  Good luck all the hunters this year.  Play safe!
That's one hell of a beauty buck Darren was this pic taken on a trail cam? Leechman
wow still fishing but after seeing that picture i think i need to dust off the bow  thanks a lot lol
hanging stands setting up blinds nxt weekend got my sites set on a beauty i have been seeing all summer  beauty buck 	best of luck harvesting him
Yep that was takin on a cam under my stand last year......while I was fishing. hope to see him this year!
